$ csc -define

The → development/languages/C-Sharp[C#] compiler option `-define` allows to define symbols whose existence can be queried at compile time in the source file with `#ifdef SYMBOL`.

Unlike in → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus[C or C++], a symbol cannot be defined to a specific value, that is, → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/preprocessor/macros[macros] are impossible.

code {
csc -define:SYMBOL                                 …
csc -define:SYMBOL_ONE;SYMBOL_TWO                  …
csc -define:SYMBOL_ONE;SYMBOL_TWO;SYMBOL_THREE     …
code }
